hackathon-description-text: TartanHacks 2017 is a hackathon at Carnegie Mellon University.
hackathon-requirements: Submissions must include all team member's names, a unique title for the project, and a brief description of your project. We also request one phone number per team so that we can contact you immediately if necessary.

hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Google "Most Likely to Make Tangible and Lasting Change"
GoDaddy "Best App that Improves STEM Education"
CMU Student Senate "Best Hack that Improves CMU Student Life"
APT "Best Use of Data to Achieve a Positive Impact on the Community"
Rockwell Automation "Hack is Made with Purpose to Improve Human's Impact on the Environment"
Capital One "Best Usage of the Capital One API"
